<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 04 at 6:20AM EDT  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>...PATCHY DENSE VALLEY FOG EARLY THIS MORNING...
Early morning surface observations and satellite imagery show
patches of fog across much of southern Connecticut, also along
the Great Swamp and Croton River areas of eastern Putnam and
northeastern Westchester Counties. The fog may be locally dense,
with visibility less than one quarter mile, especially near
rivers, lakes, and reservoirs.
Anyone out driving in these areas should be ready for sudden
visibility reductions, use fog lamps or low beam headlights if
needed, and allow extra braking distance in case of a sudden stop.</description>
